        ('900dc36f-8394-46dd-8b2d-ffb91323bf91', '{"type": "TextualBody", "value": "Τῶν δὲ δηλούντων πάθος τὰ μὲν ἔχουσι τὸ πάθος ἐνεργείᾳ, τὰ δὲ δυνάμε", "format": "text", "source": "mela:text-content:1b4452c9-15bb-49c9-9b5e-e8c29a5d1486", "language": "gr"}', 'd27d564d-c7a7-41f3-8e22-d693afecb05e', null, null, '2025-07-04 11:19:44.144', '2025-07-04 11:19:44.144'),
        ('141ca98b-ca56-4b31-8b7c-fda9c47a42f7', '{"type": "TextualBody", "value": "1 Some of the words indicate passivity, while others indicate agency, such as ποιητής (maker, doer) and ποιητός (made, done). Some words that express passivity do so in actuality, while others do so in potentiality. For example, in actuality: γνωστός, *known*, which means *the one who is known*; and in potentiality: θνητός, *mortal/ perishable*, and τρωτός, *vulnerable*, that is one who can be wounded and di", "format": "text", "source": "mela:text-content:11bf407f-6a5e-41aa-9826-b3959bd4a1f9", "language": "en"}', 'c25f6769-dd8c-49fc-b737-abe5573cf979', null, null, '2025-07-04 11:22:53.805', '2025-07-04 11:22:53.805'),
