        ('327dfc8b-10de-4bb1-a697-1b784827d1cc', '{"type": "TextualBody", "value": "“Κύριε Ἰησοῦ Χριστὲ ὁ θεὸς ἡμῶν”. How many parts of speech are there? Three. Κύριε, Ἰησοῦ, Χριστέ and θεός are nouns; ὁ, an article. ἡμῶν, a pronoun. Since two or more nouns may be joined together in a single unit, they are considered one part of speech. In the same way, multiple verbs may be also joined in one verb, and they are trated as a single part of speech; likewise, several pronouns \\<may be joined> into one, and they, too, constitute a single word in the corresponding parts of speech.", "format": "text", "source": "mela:text-content:eaf15b84-377a-430d-80bc-fbfc73d0b99d", "language": "en"}', 'a7d56733-963b-4c35-9735-f8d9f004d04b', null, null, '2025-07-08 17:26:21.610', '2025-07-08 17:26:21.610'),
